5.Types of Models
SAPUI5 supports four primary types of models to manage application data and bind it to user interfaces: JSON, OData (V2/V4), XML, and Resource models. They are categorized into client-side (JSON, XML, Resource) for local, small-to-medium data, and server-side (OData) for large, backend-connected datasets.

Key Model Types in SAPUI5
•	OData Model (sap.ui.model.odata.v2.ODataModel or v4.ODataModel):
o	Type: Server-side model.
o	Use Case: Primary model for SAP applications, connecting to backend SAP systems via OData services (V2 or V4). It supports complex queries, sorting, and filtering on the server.

•	JSON Model (sap.ui.model.json.JSONModel):
o	Type: Client-side model.
o	Use Case: Suitable for small datasets, local JSON files, or temporary data that is completely loaded on the client side. Fast and lightweight.
•	XML Model (sap.ui.model.xml.XMLModel):
o	Type: Client-side model.
o	Use Case: Used when data is in XML format. Similar to JSON model, it holds all data on the client side.
•	Resource Model (sap.ui.model.resource.ResourceModel):
o	Type: Client-side model.
o	Use Case: Specially used for handling internationalization (i18n) and binding language-dependent texts (resource bundles). [1, 2, 3, 4, 5]

