11.How we can call one application in the existing application
We have to keep one button and use the crossappnavigator.
In SAPUI5, the primary service used for cross-application navigation within the Fiori Launchpad is sap.ushell.services.CrossApplicationNavigation
This service is accessed within a controller's sap.ui.define block or via sap.ushell.Container.getService to navigate to external targets, such as another Fiori app. [1, 2]
Key Components for Cross-App Navigation
•	Service Name: CrossApplicationNavigation.
•	Library/Module: sap/ushell/services/CrossApplicationNavigation.
•	Access Point: sap.ushell.Container.getService("CrossApplicationNavigation").
•	Primary Method: .toExternal(). [1, 2, 3, 4]
Implementation in Controller (.js)
To implement cross-app navigation, you typically follow these steps in your controller:
1.	Get the Service: Check if sap.ushell exists and obtain the service.
2.	Form the Intent: Define the semantic object and action.
3.	Navigate: Call toExternal
This service is accessed within a controller's sap.ui.define block or via sap.ushell.Container.getService to navigate to external targets, such as another Fiori app.
	onHcpZycusPress: function (oEvent) {
