18.Life cycle methods (how many time it will rendering the views)
OnInit
OnBeforeRednering
OnAfterRendering
OnExit
SAPUI5 lifecycle methods (onInit, onBeforeRendering, onAfterRendering, onExit) manage controller and view behavior. onInit and onExit run exactly once per view lifecycle, while onBeforeRendering and onAfterRendering run every time the view is rendered (rendered) or re-rendered.
onInit(): Ideal for one-time initialization, such as initializing models or setting up binding.
onBeforeRendering(): Used to perform clean-up tasks or small modifications just before the HTML is placed on the screen.
onAfterRendering(): Crucial for initializing third-party libraries (e.g., D3.js) or manipulating HTML elements, as the view's HTML is now part of the DOM.
 onExit(): Used to free up resources or destroy objects to prevent memory leaks
